20+ years…. We used to be worried about Solos and who was piecing up on lunch back in high school.
Then we moved to ATL, living in a two bedroom apartment with no furniture, surviving off of @mcdonalds & @tacobell $1 menus. Hoping to get a deal, and that a label would l change our situations.
Needless to say, they didn’t change our lives, but they did change our mindsets. 
The things we saw, and the things we experienced weren’t for the weak or timid.
We took L’s together, learned together, earned together, and we yearned together.
But God wanted us to go through some of these valleys separate. So the time came when we had to take different paths. 
Now we come back like we never left , stronger, wiser,  happier, saucier, and more focused, and sure than we’ve ever been before. We had all the tools we needed the whole time we just didn’t know it.. Now we gone stunt it like it’s Show & Tell ya unndastandme‼️💯
@msjanehandcock I couldn’t be more proud of the directions we have taken, the communities and bonds that we’ve formed in aligned with, the growth we both have made., and the accomplishments we have worked for. All we needed was the confidence and how its looking today …we got that in abundance.. YOU FEEL ME‼️

If you take anything from our story, take this … never give up on yourself, walk in Faith, love on those that love on you, trust the process, and no matter what, always keep it pushing like a wheelchair ‼️ Cause this is a marathon, not a sprint. HELLOOO‼️😤
